WEBVTT

00:09:29.101 --> 00:09:33.983
And privacy was not a consideration
that was in the discussion.

00:09:34.943 --> 00:09:36.906
CA: What should have happened then?

00:09:36.930 --> 00:09:39.927
Because suddenly,
it became very, very apparent

00:09:39.951 --> 00:09:44.179
that there'd been this horrifying hack
of enormous consequence.

00:09:44.203 --> 00:09:46.179
What should have happened at that point?

00:09:46.203 --> 00:09:47.370
RM: Except, not a hack.

00:09:47.394 --> 00:09:49.933
They were using the tools
the way they were designed.

00:09:49.957 --> 00:09:52.204
Essentially, this was
the unintended consequence

00:09:52.228 --> 00:09:53.799
of a well-intended strategy,

00:09:53.823 --> 00:09:57.545
done by really bad actors
who had a really clever strategy.

00:09:57.569 --> 00:09:59.760
So when I went to them
on the 30th of October,

00:09:59.784 --> 00:10:02.303
I sent this op-ed I was drafting --